This repository contains source code that implements the VHD
(Virtual Hard Drive) file format.  Contained within is a C library and
associated tools.

This code originated from the Xen hypervisor source code tree, found under the
tools/blktap2/vhd directory.

According to the COPYING file found in the root of the Xen source code tree
(which I've duplicated in this repo), most or all of the code contained here
is licensed under GNU GPLv2.  Please read 'COPYING' for more detail.

===

libuuid and associated header files are required for building.  If building on
Debian or Ubuntu, apt-get install uuid-dev.

Code can be built by:

1) sh autogen.sh
2) ./configure
3) make

To install the library, headers, and tools, 'make install'.
